1
00:00:00,046 --> 00:00:01,513
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,513 --> 00:00:02,946
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:03,846 --> 00:00:05,413
(Lucky Joy Tech Intellectual Property
and Acquisition Agreement)

4
00:00:05,413 --> 00:00:06,413
Found it.

5
00:00:06,413 --> 00:00:07,413
(Episode 10)

6
00:00:21,313 --> 00:00:22,313
Who's that?

7
00:00:22,913 --> 00:00:23,913
Who are you?

8
00:00:28,713 --> 00:00:29,713
Who are you?

9
00:00:30,213 --> 00:00:31,213
Stay right there.

10
00:00:35,746 --> 00:00:36,746
Lucky Joy?

11
00:00:38,213 --> 00:00:39,646
What are you doing here?

12
00:00:41,213 --> 00:00:42,413
I'm sorry.

13
00:00:42,713 --> 00:00:44,813
I'm done here, so I'll get going now.

14
00:00:45,513 --> 00:00:46,513
Stop right there.

15
00:00:47,246 --> 00:00:48,646
What do you mean you're done?

16
00:00:48,846 --> 00:00:51,913
I know this is illegal.

17
00:00:52,013 --> 00:00:53,113
I know,

18
00:00:53,113 --> 00:00:54,646
but you sent that notice.

19
00:00:54,913 --> 00:00:57,713
If I'm going to respond legally,
I need to know what's in the contract.

20
00:00:57,713 --> 00:01:01,546
So you broke into my office
in the middle of the night...

21
00:01:01,746 --> 00:01:03,013
and secretly took pictures
of the contract?

22
00:01:04,813 --> 00:01:06,813
Is that brave or just reckless?

23
00:01:07,913 --> 00:01:08,913
Hand over your phone.

24
00:01:09,013 --> 00:01:10,946
- No, please. You can't!
- Seriously...

25
00:01:11,213 --> 00:01:12,213
Stay still!

26
00:01:12,613 --> 00:01:14,446
You have the right to remain silent,

27
00:01:14,613 --> 00:01:16,146
the right to an attorney,

28
00:01:16,613 --> 00:01:17,613
and then what was it again?

29
00:01:18,413 --> 00:01:21,013
He's not even a cop,
so why is he reciting the Miranda rights?

30
00:01:21,013 --> 00:01:22,046
He's scaring me.

31
00:01:22,313 --> 00:01:24,746
(Hanbi Police Station)

32
00:01:25,246 --> 00:01:28,313
Please handle this strictly
according to the law.

33
00:01:29,413 --> 00:01:31,313
You already know...

34
00:01:31,313 --> 00:01:33,446
I didn't go there with bad intentions.

35
00:01:33,713 --> 00:01:36,213
There will be no settlement or leniency.
That's it.

36
00:01:37,513 --> 00:01:39,613
Chief!

37
00:01:40,513 --> 00:01:41,746
It's no use.

38
00:01:41,913 --> 00:01:43,746
You were caught in the act,

39
00:01:43,746 --> 00:01:45,846
and we even have the illegal recording
on your phone.

40
00:01:46,513 --> 00:01:47,513
You can't get out of this.

41
00:01:48,146 --> 00:01:50,313
Then what's going to happen to me?

42
00:01:50,313 --> 00:01:52,413
You'll be punished
according to your crime.

43
00:01:54,646 --> 00:01:57,113
Is there anyone you want to call?
A lawyer or family?

44
00:01:57,446 --> 00:01:59,346
What? My family?

45
00:02:00,713 --> 00:02:02,813
About Eun Hyeong's appointment...

46
00:02:04,013 --> 00:02:05,113
It'll work out, right?

47
00:02:05,113 --> 00:02:07,813
He told us to wait.
The results aren't out yet.

48
00:02:09,513 --> 00:02:13,413
I keep telling myself it'll all work out
if I believe hard enough,

49
00:02:14,413 --> 00:02:15,913
so why do I still feel so anxious?

50
00:02:17,113 --> 00:02:19,713
Worrying won't change anything,

51
00:02:20,546 --> 00:02:21,946
so stop and go to sleep.

52
00:02:32,013 --> 00:02:33,213
Here, take this too.

53
00:02:38,646 --> 00:02:41,013
Dad, sit here and build with me.

54
00:02:42,113 --> 00:02:43,613
- Are you feeling better?
- Yes.

55
00:02:44,513 --> 00:02:47,513
Bit Na,
why don't you go help Grandma cook?

56
00:02:48,013 --> 00:02:50,313
She might be lonely cooking by herself.

57
00:02:50,313 --> 00:02:52,113
- Okay, Dad.
- Good.

58
00:02:52,713 --> 00:02:54,213
So cute.

59
00:02:58,113 --> 00:03:00,013
What is it? Do you have something to say?

60
00:03:00,913 --> 00:03:03,713
Actually, I didn't get the appointment.

61
00:03:05,013 --> 00:03:07,013
The philosophy department
is being shut down next semester.

62
00:03:07,546 --> 00:03:09,213
What? Shut down?

63
00:03:10,013 --> 00:03:12,013
They're getting rid
of the philosophy department altogether?

64
00:03:12,013 --> 00:03:13,013
Yes.

65
00:03:13,546 --> 00:03:16,513
Employment comes before academic values
these days.

66
00:03:17,513 --> 00:03:19,713
I'll give my last lecture this semester.

67
00:03:22,313 --> 00:03:23,913
How can that be?

68
00:03:24,913 --> 00:03:25,913
I'm sorry, Father.

69
00:03:28,346 --> 00:03:31,713
Why are you apologizing?
The department closing isn't your fault.

70
00:03:32,513 --> 00:03:33,813
So I was thinking...

71
00:03:34,146 --> 00:03:35,279
I have a recommendation
from the department head,

72
00:03:35,279 --> 00:03:37,213
and I'll look for openings
at other schools,

73
00:03:38,246 --> 00:03:40,146
so could we keep this from Mom for now?

74
00:03:40,146 --> 00:03:43,446
What are you talking about?
Your mom should know.

75
00:03:43,713 --> 00:03:45,413
She's not someone who wouldn't understand.

76
00:03:45,546 --> 00:03:49,313
To Mom, I have to be the perfect ideal.

77
00:03:49,946 --> 00:03:51,346
Please give me a little time.

78
00:03:52,013 --> 00:03:53,746
So that's why you drank so much.

79
00:04:05,046 --> 00:04:07,713
Dad, step somewhere private
and call me right away.

80
00:04:15,313 --> 00:04:17,713
What? The police station?

81
00:04:19,446 --> 00:04:20,446
I'm sorry.

82
00:04:20,813 --> 00:04:23,946
I was just going to copy the documents
and return the key.

83
00:04:25,713 --> 00:04:27,913
Why did you do something so reckless?

84
00:04:28,646 --> 00:04:32,413
This won't cause trouble for you too,
right?

85
00:04:32,413 --> 00:04:34,046
Is now really the time to worry about me?

86
00:04:35,746 --> 00:04:39,713
Anyway, I'll go see the chief tomorrow
and plead with him.

87
00:04:40,213 --> 00:04:42,013
He's not someone who'll listen to that.

88
00:04:42,013 --> 00:04:43,913
He's completely heartless.

89
00:04:44,113 --> 00:04:47,546
Really? He didn't seem that harsh to me.

90
00:04:48,213 --> 00:04:50,413
The person you met isn't the chief.

91
00:04:50,413 --> 00:04:53,013
He's some team manager, nobody important.

92
00:04:54,913 --> 00:04:56,746
He's my high school friend.

93
00:04:57,246 --> 00:04:58,246
Say hello.

94
00:04:59,913 --> 00:05:01,613
Hello, I'm Ko Gyeol.

95
00:05:03,713 --> 00:05:06,346
No matter what,

96
00:05:06,346 --> 00:05:08,146
I'll find a way to get you out of here.

97
00:05:08,713 --> 00:05:10,313
So stay strong.

98
00:05:11,513 --> 00:05:14,513
I'm sorry you have to see me like this,
Dad.

99
00:05:16,913 --> 00:05:19,213
What am I supposed to tell your mom?

100
00:05:19,713 --> 00:05:22,846
Come tomorrow morning,
if she finds out you didn't come home...

101
00:05:27,413 --> 00:05:29,346
Tell her I went to a developers' seminar.

102
00:05:29,613 --> 00:05:33,313
Say I got the notice suddenly
and couldn't tell her, okay?

103
00:05:33,813 --> 00:05:35,113
A developers' seminar?

104
00:05:40,813 --> 00:05:42,513
You're late. Did you meet him?

105
00:05:43,246 --> 00:05:44,513
Meet who?

106
00:05:44,913 --> 00:05:45,913
Min Ho.

107
00:05:46,213 --> 00:05:47,746
He rushed out after dinner.

108
00:05:49,013 --> 00:05:51,146
So I thought he was going to see you
at work.

109
00:05:51,446 --> 00:05:53,913
No, I didn't meet him. What about Dad?

110
00:05:54,113 --> 00:05:56,313
He told Min Ho off and seems upset.

111
00:05:56,713 --> 00:05:58,213
He's been in his study the whole time.

112
00:05:58,613 --> 00:05:59,613
Told him off about what?

113
00:05:59,613 --> 00:06:01,713
That he was being one-sided...

114
00:06:02,113 --> 00:06:04,713
and should respect your feelings.

115
00:06:06,013 --> 00:06:09,613
Honestly, I feel a little bad for Min Ho.

116
00:06:10,446 --> 00:06:12,813
Liking someone isn't a crime.

117
00:06:15,146 --> 00:06:16,146
Darn it.

118
00:06:23,546 --> 00:06:25,046
No, it's fine.

119
00:06:25,213 --> 00:06:27,046
My laptop didn't get wet, so don't worry.

120
00:06:33,646 --> 00:06:35,246
What are you doing? Let go of my hand.

121
00:06:39,746 --> 00:06:41,513
You pervert!

122
00:06:43,913 --> 00:06:45,413
I'll get my revenge.

123
00:06:46,346 --> 00:06:49,113
I'll tear you to pieces.

124
00:06:49,646 --> 00:06:51,913
I'll completely destroy you!

125
00:06:54,213 --> 00:06:55,213
What are you doing?

126
00:06:56,713 --> 00:06:58,113
What happened to your promise with me?

127
00:06:59,313 --> 00:07:00,313
Promise?

128
00:07:02,613 --> 00:07:03,613
The progress report.

129
00:07:04,513 --> 00:07:06,613
I was actually going to show you today.

130
00:07:06,613 --> 00:07:08,213
I was preparing a masterpiece.

131
00:07:09,213 --> 00:07:11,913
But because of some crazy girl...

132
00:07:13,313 --> 00:07:15,346
A promise is meant to be kept.

133
00:07:15,846 --> 00:07:19,246
If you don't send it by tomorrow,
no allowance this month. Got it?

134
00:07:22,413 --> 00:07:25,146
Hey, isn't that my cardigan?

135
00:07:26,846 --> 00:07:29,513
Sorry, I forgot.
I was going to put it back.

136
00:07:30,846 --> 00:07:31,846
Here.

137
00:07:32,646 --> 00:07:35,213
How am I supposed to wear it
when it's all stretched out?

138
00:07:37,313 --> 00:07:38,313
Thanks.

139
00:07:39,513 --> 00:07:41,313
Why you little...

140
00:07:41,313 --> 00:07:42,413
You idiot!

141
00:07:43,046 --> 00:07:44,213
Stop hitting me already.

142
00:07:44,546 --> 00:07:46,913
I can't tell
if you're my sister or a thug.

143
00:07:47,913 --> 00:07:49,113
You deserve it.

144
00:07:49,113 --> 00:07:50,646
Yeah, I'm a thug.

145
00:07:52,746 --> 00:07:54,746
Don't forget your promise.

146
00:07:55,413 --> 00:07:58,713
I'll keep it. I said I'll keep it.

147
00:08:01,946 --> 00:08:03,013
You wench.

148
00:08:03,013 --> 00:08:05,646
Hey, you did seduce my boyfriend!

149
00:08:06,146 --> 00:08:07,546
And you call yourself a friend?

150
00:08:07,946 --> 00:08:09,413
Seduce him, my foot.

151
00:08:09,646 --> 00:08:11,913
That jerk came onto me,
saying you two were done.

152
00:08:11,913 --> 00:08:13,246
What? That jerk?

153
00:08:13,513 --> 00:08:15,646
Did you just call my boyfriend a jerk?

154
00:08:16,346 --> 00:08:17,446
You little...

155
00:08:18,013 --> 00:08:19,513
Let go of me!

156
00:08:21,146 --> 00:08:22,713
- You...
- Hey, you teenagers!

157
00:08:23,313 --> 00:08:25,513
You're so loud! I'm about to lose it!

158
00:08:26,513 --> 00:08:28,513
I already have too much on my mind...

159
00:08:28,513 --> 00:08:30,013
and feel like my head's about to explode.

160
00:08:30,013 --> 00:08:32,513
Did you rent this place out or what?

161
00:08:32,513 --> 00:08:33,513
Hey!

162
00:08:33,913 --> 00:08:36,513
You're louder! Be quiet.

163
00:08:40,213 --> 00:08:41,213
I'm sorry.

164
00:08:46,813 --> 00:08:48,713
What do I do now?

165
00:08:51,146 --> 00:08:52,146
Joy.

166
00:08:52,146 --> 00:08:53,013
(How can I help you?)

167
00:08:53,013 --> 00:08:54,546
Can you find
a traditional bindaetteok place...

168
00:08:54,546 --> 00:08:57,413
with mung beans ground on a millstone,

169
00:08:57,913 --> 00:09:00,913
loaded with kimchi, pork,
and bean sprouts?

170
00:09:01,046 --> 00:09:02,046
Of course.

171
00:09:02,413 --> 00:09:05,413
I'll connect you with someone who makes...

172
00:09:05,413 --> 00:09:06,613
traditional bindaetteok themselves.

173
00:09:07,046 --> 00:09:08,113
Just a moment.

174
00:09:08,513 --> 00:09:09,913
Connect me?

175
00:09:10,913 --> 00:09:11,913
Hello.

176
00:09:12,213 --> 00:09:15,846
I run Grandma's Bindaetteok. Who is this?

177
00:09:16,813 --> 00:09:19,613
Right. Hello.

178
00:09:20,213 --> 00:09:21,513
I asked Joy...

179
00:09:22,513 --> 00:09:25,446
to recommend
an old-style bindaetteok place.

180
00:09:26,746 --> 00:09:29,813
Joy is very smart, isn't she?

181
00:09:32,546 --> 00:09:34,513
I'll give you the address,

182
00:09:34,746 --> 00:09:36,846
- so come by sometime.
- Yes.

183
00:09:36,846 --> 00:09:40,413
I know I'm bragging,
but it's really delicious.

184
00:09:41,713 --> 00:09:43,546
Yes, please give me the address.

185
00:09:46,613 --> 00:09:47,613
Yes.

186
00:09:50,313 --> 00:09:52,546
Okay.

187
00:09:53,446 --> 00:09:56,313
I'll come by soon. Goodbye.

188
00:09:56,846 --> 00:09:57,913
What are you doing, Grandma?

189
00:09:59,013 --> 00:10:00,013
This...

190
00:10:00,813 --> 00:10:03,613
is an AI for seniors,

191
00:10:04,146 --> 00:10:05,346
so I'm trying it out.

192
00:10:08,113 --> 00:10:10,446
This is Lucky Joy.

193
00:10:11,413 --> 00:10:14,813
These days, seeing an old lady...

194
00:10:14,813 --> 00:10:17,013
sitting down on the street
isn't a big deal.

195
00:10:17,646 --> 00:10:19,913
But she was so kind and caring.

196
00:10:20,646 --> 00:10:23,113
You don't see people like that these days.

197
00:10:24,513 --> 00:10:27,213
She said she made this herself?

198
00:10:27,213 --> 00:10:28,413
That's what she said.

199
00:10:29,513 --> 00:10:32,813
But she said something came up...

200
00:10:33,613 --> 00:10:35,313
and she can't continue developing it.

201
00:10:35,846 --> 00:10:38,846
Do you happen to know her name?

202
00:10:39,713 --> 00:10:42,313
I don't. I should've at least asked.

203
00:10:43,146 --> 00:10:44,613
I only received her help.

204
00:10:45,513 --> 00:10:48,913
It's late. Go to your room and sleep.

205
00:10:48,913 --> 00:10:50,146
Grandpa must be waiting for me.

206
00:10:50,146 --> 00:10:51,813
Yes, good night, Grandma.

207
00:11:06,513 --> 00:11:08,946
You're late. Were you
at Mr. Seo's house this whole time?

208
00:11:10,046 --> 00:11:11,513
What if I was?

209
00:11:11,513 --> 00:11:13,513
Why are you talking like that?
I'll go up first.

210
00:11:13,813 --> 00:11:15,146
I'm coming from the police station.

211
00:11:17,513 --> 00:11:19,846
The police station? Why?

212
00:11:19,946 --> 00:11:22,413
You know that woman who mistook you
for the chief?

213
00:11:22,746 --> 00:11:24,046
The Lucky Joy developer?

214
00:11:24,046 --> 00:11:25,313
Yeah, that psycho.

215
00:11:27,013 --> 00:11:29,813
I should've known what she was like
when she gave you a nosebleed.

216
00:11:30,846 --> 00:11:32,946
What is it? What happened?

217
00:11:35,113 --> 00:11:36,213
A developers' seminar?

218
00:11:36,713 --> 00:11:38,746
Yeah, I guess it got decided suddenly.

219
00:11:39,113 --> 00:11:40,646
It'll take about three or four days.

220
00:11:41,013 --> 00:11:42,946
That girl didn't say a word to me.

221
00:11:44,413 --> 00:11:47,013
She took the night train,
so she's probably asleep by now.

222
00:11:47,346 --> 00:11:48,546
And her schedule's packed...

223
00:11:48,546 --> 00:11:50,613
from morning till night,

224
00:11:51,013 --> 00:11:52,146
so she said
she won't be able to answer her phone.

225
00:11:53,413 --> 00:11:54,646
Did Eun Ae go to a seminar?

226
00:11:54,646 --> 00:11:57,046
Apparently. She didn't tell you either?

227
00:11:57,046 --> 00:11:59,213
No, and I was up late.

228
00:12:00,013 --> 00:12:01,846
I don't think I heard her leave.

229
00:12:02,813 --> 00:12:05,646
She probably left quietly
so she wouldn't wake anyone.

230
00:12:06,013 --> 00:12:07,213
How did you find out?

231
00:12:07,446 --> 00:12:08,446
Me?

232
00:12:10,046 --> 00:12:11,213
I couldn't sleep,

233
00:12:11,913 --> 00:12:14,046
so I went out to the yard for some air
and ran into her.

234
00:12:15,913 --> 00:12:18,046
I'm late. I'll get going.

235
00:12:18,713 --> 00:12:19,846
Okay, take care.

236
00:12:20,213 --> 00:12:21,913
- Bye, Dad.
- See you.

237
00:12:24,346 --> 00:12:27,146
But why has Dad been going to work
at dawn every day lately?

238
00:12:27,413 --> 00:12:29,546
He's going to the pool before work.

239
00:12:29,846 --> 00:12:32,346
He says he's put on weight
around the belly.

240
00:12:35,313 --> 00:12:37,546
I should start exercising too.

241
00:12:38,613 --> 00:12:40,113
Not just breathing or walking,

242
00:12:40,813 --> 00:12:42,713
and not housework. Real exercise.

243
00:12:43,213 --> 00:12:45,913
Sure. If you want to keep studying
what you love,

244
00:12:45,913 --> 00:12:47,246
you need to exercise.

245
00:12:47,913 --> 00:12:50,413
Even your brain needs your body moving
to stay healthy.

246
00:12:50,813 --> 00:12:54,313
If Dr. Cho says so,
I guess I should start doing something.

247
00:12:55,213 --> 00:12:56,213
Not again!

248
00:12:56,813 --> 00:12:59,246
I'm not a doctor.

249
00:12:59,613 --> 00:13:00,846
What should I make you for breakfast?

250
00:13:01,213 --> 00:13:02,713
Sandwich? Porridge?

251
00:13:03,246 --> 00:13:04,613
(Kangsu Construction)

252
00:13:04,613 --> 00:13:05,913
It's entirely my fault.

253
00:13:06,913 --> 00:13:09,913
I failed to return the master key...

254
00:13:09,913 --> 00:13:11,513
and took it home with me.

255
00:13:12,846 --> 00:13:16,213
My daughter thought
she needed to see the documents...

256
00:13:16,213 --> 00:13:17,713
to respond properly,

257
00:13:19,213 --> 00:13:20,946
so she ended up committing
a serious mistake.

258
00:13:21,646 --> 00:13:22,646
So?

259
00:13:24,613 --> 00:13:26,513
Please forgive her this once.

260
00:13:26,846 --> 00:13:28,213
She has a bright future ahead of her.

261
00:13:28,513 --> 00:13:29,646
If this goes on, she could...

262
00:13:30,413 --> 00:13:31,413
Listen.

263
00:13:32,113 --> 00:13:33,713
If I wanted to,

264
00:13:34,446 --> 00:13:37,313
I could cancel
your company's service contract over this.

265
00:13:38,746 --> 00:13:40,346
Because she used
a service staff's master key,

266
00:13:40,713 --> 00:13:43,313
she nearly caused a major incident
involving leaked confidential documents.

267
00:13:44,113 --> 00:13:45,113
Yes, I understand.

268
00:13:45,313 --> 00:13:48,346
I sincerely apologize for that, but...

269
00:13:48,346 --> 00:13:50,313
Then should I just have
all the service staff...

270
00:13:50,313 --> 00:13:51,513
fired altogether?

271
00:13:52,146 --> 00:13:53,146
What?

272
00:13:54,546 --> 00:13:55,813
No, that can't happen.

273
00:13:56,213 --> 00:13:57,613
Because of my mistake,

274
00:13:57,613 --> 00:14:00,313
I can't let the others
lose their jobs too.

275
00:14:00,713 --> 00:14:02,013
Then get back to work.

276
00:14:03,846 --> 00:14:05,246
Chief, please.

277
00:14:05,913 --> 00:14:07,213
Didn't you hear me tell you to leave?

278
00:14:17,413 --> 00:14:18,413
Hello.

279
00:14:31,046 --> 00:14:32,046
Do you know him?

280
00:14:33,446 --> 00:14:35,113
No. Let's go in.

281
00:14:37,513 --> 00:14:40,313
What happened?
You even came to me on your own.

282
00:14:40,913 --> 00:14:43,313
I was just about to call you anyway
to tell you something.

283
00:14:44,646 --> 00:14:45,646
Something?

284
00:14:46,246 --> 00:14:48,413
About the other day...

285
00:14:48,413 --> 00:14:50,146
I'm sorry about that.

286
00:14:51,013 --> 00:14:53,146
I got carried away with my emotions,

287
00:14:53,613 --> 00:14:55,913
and I didn't realize my goodwill...

288
00:14:55,913 --> 00:14:57,713
could be a burden to you. I'm sorry.

289
00:14:59,713 --> 00:15:00,913
Same here.

290
00:15:00,913 --> 00:15:03,313
I couldn't accept your feelings properly.

291
00:15:04,013 --> 00:15:05,146
Let's just forget it.

292
00:15:06,113 --> 00:15:07,346
What's gotten into you?

293
00:15:07,513 --> 00:15:10,046
You looked like
you were about to quit that day.

294
00:15:11,313 --> 00:15:13,146
How could I? I've got a family.

295
00:15:14,013 --> 00:15:15,213
I still have a lot to do.

296
00:15:15,213 --> 00:15:16,413
Right.

297
00:15:16,946 --> 00:15:19,813
And if anything comes up,

298
00:15:19,813 --> 00:15:22,113
tell me anytime without hesitation.

299
00:15:22,846 --> 00:15:25,113
I won't step in first...

300
00:15:25,113 --> 00:15:26,713
since it seems like you don't want that,

301
00:15:27,713 --> 00:15:29,113
but I'd appreciate it if you tell me.

302
00:15:30,513 --> 00:15:31,546
Okay, I will.

303
00:15:32,513 --> 00:15:33,513
Well...

304
00:15:35,113 --> 00:15:36,113
Actually...

305
00:15:41,513 --> 00:15:43,513
The chairman is asking you to come.

306
00:15:44,513 --> 00:15:45,813
Right now?

307
00:15:46,113 --> 00:15:47,113
Yes.

308
00:15:48,346 --> 00:15:49,313
Mr. Ju,

309
00:15:49,313 --> 00:15:51,446
don't you remember him?

310
00:15:52,013 --> 00:15:55,046
Back in high school,
he'd come by the house all the time...

311
00:15:55,046 --> 00:15:57,013
with Gwon Sik. He's one of the trio.

312
00:15:58,913 --> 00:16:00,746
Wait, are you that older guy?

313
00:16:04,013 --> 00:16:05,013
Hello.

314
00:16:06,113 --> 00:16:07,746
That's right. That was Mr. Ju.

315
00:16:07,746 --> 00:16:09,713
We called him Yong Man.

316
00:16:11,546 --> 00:16:12,613
Don't you remember him?

317
00:16:13,946 --> 00:16:16,113
Well, it's been over 40 years.

318
00:16:16,113 --> 00:16:17,313
I understand.

319
00:16:17,713 --> 00:16:19,513
We saw each other 25 years ago too.

320
00:16:20,913 --> 00:16:23,013
You haven't changed at all.

321
00:16:23,913 --> 00:16:25,413
Except for some gray hair.

322
00:16:27,613 --> 00:16:29,113
What? 25 years ago?

323
00:16:30,313 --> 00:16:32,513
You're getting confused again.

324
00:16:33,413 --> 00:16:34,813
Anyway, Seong Jun,

325
00:16:34,813 --> 00:16:37,613
I have to go to the chairman's office,
so I'll go first.

326
00:16:37,913 --> 00:16:39,313
Yeah, okay.

327
00:16:39,313 --> 00:16:40,313
Okay.

328
00:16:40,613 --> 00:16:41,813
- Have a good day.
- Bye.

329
00:16:57,613 --> 00:17:00,146
Is this the person...

330
00:17:00,713 --> 00:17:01,913
who trespassed into Chief Ko's office?

331
00:17:02,446 --> 00:17:05,713
Yes, she was caught taking photos
of the acquisition contract...

332
00:17:06,013 --> 00:17:07,713
and is currently being detained
at the police station.

333
00:17:08,013 --> 00:17:10,246
What? What on earth...

334
00:17:12,113 --> 00:17:14,613
I thought you had given final approval,
President Ko.

335
00:17:15,146 --> 00:17:17,313
Didn't you find any issues
during the acquisition?

336
00:17:17,313 --> 00:17:19,513
No, there were no issues at all.

337
00:17:19,513 --> 00:17:21,713
It was clearly a lawful acquisition.

338
00:17:21,713 --> 00:17:23,313
Then why is this happening...

339
00:17:23,313 --> 00:17:25,113
if there was nothing wrong?

340
00:17:26,213 --> 00:17:27,213
I'm sorry.

341
00:17:27,546 --> 00:17:29,613
I'll confirm the facts
through the chief...

342
00:17:30,313 --> 00:17:31,713
and take immediate action.

343
00:17:39,913 --> 00:17:41,513
Why are you doing this to me?

344
00:17:41,846 --> 00:17:44,013
Is it that hard to come to me first...

345
00:17:44,013 --> 00:17:45,746
before reporting to the chairman?

346
00:17:46,546 --> 00:17:48,046
I was just doing my job.

347
00:17:51,813 --> 00:17:52,813
Seo Gwon Sik!

348
00:17:57,213 --> 00:17:59,213
What? Show her leniency?

349
00:17:59,413 --> 00:18:04,246
Yes. Since we didn't confirm
both co-CEOs' consent before proceeding,

350
00:18:04,246 --> 00:18:05,413
we also bear some responsibility.

351
00:18:05,413 --> 00:18:06,746
Even so,

352
00:18:07,246 --> 00:18:09,813
she broke into my office
and stole documents.

353
00:18:10,613 --> 00:18:12,046
That's clearly theft.

354
00:18:13,513 --> 00:18:15,146
If we handle this strictly by the law,

355
00:18:15,146 --> 00:18:16,546
what will happen to the developer?

356
00:18:16,546 --> 00:18:20,246
What do you mean?
She'll pay for what she did.

357
00:18:21,613 --> 00:18:22,913
Please reconsider, Chief.

358
00:18:23,413 --> 00:18:26,113
The method was wrong,
but the situation is understandable.

359
00:18:26,113 --> 00:18:28,913
This isn't something we can overlook
out of sympathy.

360
00:18:29,446 --> 00:18:30,813
If we let it slide again,

361
00:18:31,213 --> 00:18:34,246
who knows what she'll do next?

362
00:18:34,246 --> 00:18:38,113
That's why I think
it should be handled quietly.

363
00:18:38,713 --> 00:18:39,713
Quietly?

364
00:18:40,913 --> 00:18:42,613
Do you think that psycho
will back down quietly?

365
00:18:42,713 --> 00:18:44,713
If it goes to trial, it'll be in the news,

366
00:18:44,946 --> 00:18:47,113
and that won't help the company's image.

367
00:18:47,846 --> 00:18:50,413
Also, the chairman will find out.

368
00:18:51,013 --> 00:18:52,113
Are you okay with that?

369
00:18:55,346 --> 00:18:56,413
Then how do you suggest...

370
00:18:57,813 --> 00:18:59,713
we handle it quietly?

371
00:19:06,013 --> 00:19:07,013
Get back to work.

372
00:19:16,146 --> 00:19:17,613
What is going on?

373
00:19:18,813 --> 00:19:21,013
"What's going on?"
That's what you're asking?

374
00:19:27,513 --> 00:19:30,713
I don't even want to set foot there again,

375
00:19:31,913 --> 00:19:33,446
but it's not that simple.

376
00:19:34,013 --> 00:19:36,613
So you made hangover soup,
marinated bulgogi,

377
00:19:36,613 --> 00:19:39,746
and prepared a ton of side dishes?

378
00:19:40,113 --> 00:19:42,446
What else could I do? He kept throwing up.

379
00:19:43,013 --> 00:19:44,346
I had to make something for his stomach.

380
00:19:46,013 --> 00:19:48,213
Kids are kings.

381
00:19:48,413 --> 00:19:51,213
They say it's better not to have kids
for a reason.

382
00:19:52,046 --> 00:19:55,046
Why did he drink so much anyway?

383
00:19:55,046 --> 00:19:56,846
He must be stressed too.

384
00:19:57,346 --> 00:20:00,513
He's been on the verge of getting
a professorship for years now.

385
00:20:01,213 --> 00:20:02,213
I can understand.

386
00:20:03,213 --> 00:20:05,513
That must be tough.

387
00:20:06,113 --> 00:20:09,246
By the way, did you know...

388
00:20:09,746 --> 00:20:11,913
that Eun Ae went to a seminar last night?

389
00:20:12,346 --> 00:20:13,846
What? A seminar?

390
00:20:14,113 --> 00:20:15,446
She didn't tell you either?

391
00:20:15,846 --> 00:20:19,113
No. That's strange.
She didn't say anything yesterday.

392
00:20:19,713 --> 00:20:21,813
You saw her yesterday? Around what time?

393
00:20:22,913 --> 00:20:26,113
Right after dinner, so around 8 p.m.

394
00:20:33,013 --> 00:20:34,013
What are you doing?

395
00:20:34,813 --> 00:20:35,846
Going night hiking or something?

396
00:20:36,646 --> 00:20:38,346
Do I look like I have time for hiking?

397
00:20:39,013 --> 00:20:40,413
Then what's with that outfit?

398
00:20:41,913 --> 00:20:42,913
Cho Rong,

399
00:20:43,813 --> 00:20:45,646
if something happens to me,

400
00:20:46,046 --> 00:20:47,846
all my assets are yours.

401
00:20:49,313 --> 00:20:51,246
Your assets? You've got nothing.

402
00:20:52,013 --> 00:20:54,513
My computer, my clothes,

403
00:20:55,213 --> 00:20:57,013
and all the treasures inside.

404
00:20:57,346 --> 00:20:59,646
They're all yours. Got it?

405
00:21:01,146 --> 00:21:04,046
Those old headbands, hair ties,
and keychains?

406
00:21:04,613 --> 00:21:06,013
Stop. You're making me tear up.

407
00:21:06,413 --> 00:21:08,013
So where are you going?

408
00:21:09,413 --> 00:21:11,813
Doesn't look like you're going to jump off
the Hangang River dressed like that.

409
00:21:12,513 --> 00:21:13,513
I'll tell you when I get back.

410
00:21:14,613 --> 00:21:16,713
Pray for my soul... No.

411
00:21:17,713 --> 00:21:18,746
Wish me luck.

412
00:21:21,213 --> 00:21:23,913
Who told you she went to a seminar?

413
00:21:24,013 --> 00:21:25,113
Her dad.

414
00:21:26,613 --> 00:21:28,046
He said she took the night train.

415
00:21:28,213 --> 00:21:30,213
He said she went out quietly
so she wouldn't wake us.

416
00:21:31,813 --> 00:21:33,913
How busy could she be
that she even turned off her phone?

417
00:21:36,246 --> 00:21:37,646
I'll step out for a bit.

418
00:21:40,746 --> 00:21:43,413
That clumsy girl.

419
00:21:45,813 --> 00:21:47,713
I wonder if...

420
00:21:48,013 --> 00:21:50,913
she'll even find someone before I die.

421
00:21:51,113 --> 00:21:54,313
Why? She's such a kind and cute girl.

422
00:21:54,946 --> 00:21:57,913
Then try setting her up.

423
00:21:58,513 --> 00:22:01,313
She's never even dated at her age.

424
00:22:01,646 --> 00:22:03,146
How's she supposed to live like that?

425
00:22:06,413 --> 00:22:08,046
Mr. Cho, it's Cho Rong.

426
00:22:08,313 --> 00:22:10,446
Do you know where Eun Ae is right now?

427
00:22:12,213 --> 00:22:13,213
What?

428
00:22:14,813 --> 00:22:17,313
Mother, I'm going out for a bit.

429
00:22:18,546 --> 00:22:21,613
Where are you going at this hour?
Everyone will be home soon.

430
00:22:21,813 --> 00:22:23,446
I'm going to stop by Seung Ri's place.

431
00:22:24,213 --> 00:22:26,246
Min Ho kept insisting I apologize.

432
00:22:26,413 --> 00:22:28,146
Good thinking.

433
00:22:28,646 --> 00:22:30,146
You need to resolve things.

434
00:22:31,513 --> 00:22:35,046
They say parents can't win
against their children. That's so true.

435
00:22:35,813 --> 00:22:36,913
Wait.

436
00:22:44,113 --> 00:22:46,813
Take this to Seung Ri's place.

437
00:22:47,613 --> 00:22:49,346
Jeong Ran always gives us food.

438
00:22:50,313 --> 00:22:52,613
It's perfectly fermented,
so it'll taste great.

439
00:22:52,613 --> 00:22:53,613
My goodness.

440
00:22:53,613 --> 00:22:56,946
You want me to carry this smelly thing?

441
00:22:56,946 --> 00:22:58,313
You're not walking.

442
00:22:58,513 --> 00:23:00,146
You have a car. What's the problem?

443
00:23:00,146 --> 00:23:01,813
Still.

444
00:23:02,046 --> 00:23:04,313
What if the smell gets into my car?

445
00:23:04,313 --> 00:23:07,613
It's in a tightly sealed container.
Please do me this favor.

446
00:23:08,246 --> 00:23:10,113
Still, with this outfit...

447
00:23:12,513 --> 00:23:13,513
Fine.

448
00:23:17,846 --> 00:23:18,846
See you later.

449
00:23:25,813 --> 00:23:27,713
What are you doing? Take it.

450
00:23:27,713 --> 00:23:28,813
It's heavy.

451
00:23:32,346 --> 00:23:33,413
What is this?

452
00:23:33,713 --> 00:23:35,446
Kimchi, obviously.

453
00:23:36,246 --> 00:23:38,713
She said it's perfectly fermented.

454
00:23:39,413 --> 00:23:41,813
Please tell her I said thank you.

455
00:23:42,713 --> 00:23:43,713
My goodness.

456
00:23:43,913 --> 00:23:45,813
I'm the one who carried it
all the way here,

457
00:23:45,813 --> 00:23:48,446
and you won't thank me?

458
00:23:53,113 --> 00:23:55,246
What brings you here,

459
00:23:55,246 --> 00:23:56,346
carrying something so heavy?

460
00:23:56,646 --> 00:23:58,346
Aren't you being a bit much?

461
00:23:59,046 --> 00:24:01,513
You haven't shown your face
for over a week...

462
00:24:01,813 --> 00:24:02,913
or even called once.

463
00:24:03,046 --> 00:24:04,413
I wasn't feeling well.

464
00:24:05,546 --> 00:24:07,213
I'm not your personal secretary.

465
00:24:07,513 --> 00:24:08,846
I don't need to check in.

466
00:24:10,346 --> 00:24:13,246
You really hold grudges, don't you?

467
00:24:13,946 --> 00:24:15,646
Let it go, okay?

468
00:24:15,646 --> 00:24:17,846
Be cool like me.

469
00:24:24,213 --> 00:24:25,313
I'm home.

470
00:24:26,613 --> 00:24:28,113
You're early today.

471
00:24:28,246 --> 00:24:30,146
I was tired, so I came home early.

472
00:24:32,813 --> 00:24:35,413
Hey. It's me, Min Ho's mom.

473
00:24:36,746 --> 00:24:37,813
Hello.

474
00:24:44,513 --> 00:24:46,613
I'm really sorry about that day.

475
00:24:47,213 --> 00:24:49,413
I have a fiery temper.

476
00:24:50,313 --> 00:24:52,846
When I heard you threw water on Min Ho,

477
00:24:52,846 --> 00:24:54,046
I just lost it.

478
00:24:55,913 --> 00:24:59,513
I'm not saying I did nothing wrong.

479
00:24:59,913 --> 00:25:01,113
I understand.

480
00:25:01,113 --> 00:25:04,046
Since you came to apologize,
I'll let it go.

481
00:25:04,413 --> 00:25:07,013
Right? You're not like your mom.

482
00:25:07,013 --> 00:25:09,313
You're cool like me. I like that.

483
00:25:11,146 --> 00:25:13,713
Here, this is my apology gift.

484
00:25:14,713 --> 00:25:15,846
What is it?

485
00:25:16,113 --> 00:25:17,113
A bag.

486
00:25:17,113 --> 00:25:20,046
I picked the youngest-looking one I have.

487
00:25:20,046 --> 00:25:21,613
It'll suit you.

488
00:25:23,913 --> 00:25:26,113
What are you doing? Take it.

489
00:25:26,113 --> 00:25:27,346
My arm hurts.

490
00:25:28,813 --> 00:25:30,913
I will not be accepting your apology.

491
00:25:31,813 --> 00:25:32,846
Hey!

492
00:25:33,113 --> 00:25:34,913
You accepted the verbal apology,

493
00:25:34,913 --> 00:25:35,946
so why refuse this?

494
00:25:36,913 --> 00:25:37,946
Is it because it's secondhand?

495
00:25:39,246 --> 00:25:42,113
I only used it twice.
It's practically new.

496
00:25:42,413 --> 00:25:43,513
Even on the resale market...

497
00:25:43,513 --> 00:25:44,913
Please leave, madam.

498
00:25:45,313 --> 00:25:46,313
Fine.

499
00:25:46,513 --> 00:25:48,813
I won't give it to you.

500
00:25:50,213 --> 00:25:52,713
But you did accept my apology, right?

501
00:25:54,213 --> 00:25:55,413
I need to change.

502
00:25:55,813 --> 00:25:59,146
And make sure to tell Min Ho...

503
00:25:59,446 --> 00:26:02,613
that I came in person to apologize, okay?

504
00:26:02,613 --> 00:26:04,013
I will.

505
00:26:07,213 --> 00:26:08,213
Seung Ri,

506
00:26:10,613 --> 00:26:12,513
why do you dislike Min Ho so much?

507
00:26:13,313 --> 00:26:14,813
- Sorry?
- I mean...

508
00:26:14,913 --> 00:26:18,013
I'm thankful to you
for not accepting his feelings.

509
00:26:18,013 --> 00:26:19,613
Merci beaucoup.

510
00:26:20,713 --> 00:26:22,013
But I'm curious.

511
00:26:22,713 --> 00:26:24,446
What's wrong with Min Ho?

512
00:26:26,946 --> 00:26:30,113
Don't ever change your mind, okay?

513
00:26:36,413 --> 00:26:37,213
(Hanbi Police Station)

514
00:26:37,213 --> 00:26:39,446
The defendant Cho Eun Ae...

515
00:26:39,446 --> 00:26:41,313
is sentenced to ten years in prison...

516
00:26:41,913 --> 00:26:44,846
for assault, property damage,
spreading false information,

517
00:26:44,846 --> 00:26:47,613
trespassing,
and violation of economic laws.

518
00:26:51,613 --> 00:26:52,646
Get inside, 6835.

519
00:26:53,113 --> 00:26:54,313
No!

520
00:26:54,313 --> 00:26:55,546
No!

521
00:26:55,813 --> 00:26:58,213
No!

522
00:26:59,346 --> 00:27:00,346
No!

523
00:27:07,213 --> 00:27:08,213
What a relief.

524
00:27:10,046 --> 00:27:11,413
Cho Eun Ae, you have a visitor.

525
00:27:12,213 --> 00:27:15,313
A visitor? Who?

526
00:27:16,313 --> 00:27:18,813
What did you just say? Intern?

527
00:27:19,146 --> 00:27:21,113
Yes, a six-month temporary position.

528
00:27:21,113 --> 00:27:24,046
An intern in Strategic Planning
at Kangsu Construction.

529
00:27:29,646 --> 00:27:30,646
You!

530
00:27:36,146 --> 00:27:37,613
Me?

531
00:27:37,746 --> 00:27:39,213
Yes, you.

532
00:27:53,246 --> 00:27:55,913
(Our Happy Days)

533
00:27:56,146 --> 00:27:58,413
How about giving that developer a chance?

534
00:27:58,413 --> 00:28:00,746
Are you suggesting we recruit her?

535
00:28:00,746 --> 00:28:02,613
I'll take responsibility.

536
00:28:02,613 --> 00:28:03,713
Calm down, Cho Eun Ae.

537
00:28:03,713 --> 00:28:05,013
It's not over yet.

538
00:28:05,013 --> 00:28:06,546
But what made you...

539
00:28:06,546 --> 00:28:07,846
decide to ask me out first?

540
00:28:07,846 --> 00:28:09,246
